Jute fibres are harvested from jute plants that are grown from jute seeds at level 13 Farming.

Farmers can be paid 6 barley malts to watch over the hops patch for the player.

According to the book Gielinor's flora - hops, the people of Hosidius are known to create a stew from the jute plant known as Molo, although it is currently unavailable in game.

Uses[edit | edit source]

  • Ten jute fibres can be used as payment for a farmer to watch an allotment of sweetcorn.
  • Four can be woven into a empty sack using a loom. This requires a Crafting level of 21 and grants 38 experience.
  • Two can be woven into a drift net using a loom. This requires a Crafting level of 26 and grants 55 experience.
  • You need to plant some jute for an easy Kandarin Diary task.
